column1: #Text=Melbourne 's inner south contains a number of suburbs and places worthy of a visit .
#Text=The landscape varies from industrial ports to glitzy waterfront localities .
#Text=South Melbourne forms the core , along with Port Melbourne .
#Text=Albert Park is centred around a large lake in Albert Park , and is home to the famous Grand Prix Circuit .
#Text=South Melbourne is a secret jewel of Melbourne .
#Text=Centred around Clarendon Street , an extension of Spencer Street , the whole district has been settled by Greeks and Italians , quite close to where they first landed at the Port of Melbourne .

#Text=Home to magnificent examples of the late Victorian era of architecture and one of the cities wealthiest suburbs , Albert Park is known internationally as the location for the Australian Formula One Grand Prix , a road circuit which circumnavigates Albert Park Lake .
#Text=Albert Park is bordered by the suburbs of Port Melbourne to the west , South Melbourne to the north , Middle Park to the east and Port Phillip Bay to the south .
#Text=St Vincent 's Gardens and the surrounding Victorian architecture is a sight to behold .
#Text=There are abundant traveling options : trams , trains , buses and ferries .
#Text=Tram route 1 terminates at South Melbourne beach , while tram routes 12 , 58 and 96 also go through the inner south .
#Text=Clarendon Street has heaps of shops of all varieties .
#Text=A large food and retail market , with lots of shops selling fresh food as well as delis , cafes and clothes shops .
#Text=It retains many of the features of yesteryear .
#Text=An eclectic mix of 20th-century decorative and household items .
#Text=Stock can include some relatively inexpensive home furnishings .
#Text=Avenue Bookstore , 127 Dundas Place , Albert Park , ☏ +61396902227 , ✉ info@avenuebookstore.com.au .
#Text=This excellent bookstore has a wide range of well selected works .
#Text=The Sebel Citigate Albert Park Melbourne , 65 Queens Road , ☏ +61395294300 .
#Text=The Albert Park hotel is ideally located opposite Albert Park Lake , home of Australia ’s Grand Prix track .
#Text=A modern Albert Park hotel moments from St Kilda Road business district and a short tram ride to Melbourne 's CBD .
#Text=Lovely 3 bedroom apartment located just around the corner from the vibrant Victoria Avenue .
